etymologies: late 19th century; earliest use found in American Journal of Science. After German Pseudobrookit

definitions: A rare black to reddish-brown mineral which resembles brookite and occurs in volcanic rocks as small tabular or acicular crystals.

notes.text: Pseudobrookite is an oxide of titanium and ferric iron, Fe₂TiO₅. Crystal system: orthorhombic.
